## TL;DR

```console
helm install my-agentregistry oci://ghcr.io/agentregistry-dev/helm/agentregistry
```

## Introduction

This chart bootstraps an [Agent Registry](https://github.com/agentregistry-dev/agentregistry) deployment on a [Kubernetes](https://kubernetes.io) cluster using the [Helm](https://helm.sh) package manager.

It includes a bundled [pgvector/pgvector](https://hub.docker.com/r/pgvector/pgvector) sidecar (PostgreSQL + pgvector extension) and exposes both an HTTP REST API and an Agent Gateway gRPC endpoint.

## Prerequisites

- Kubernetes 1.19+
- Helm 3.8+
- PV provisioner support in the underlying infrastructure (for bundled PostgreSQL persistence)

## Installing the Chart

```console
helm install my-agentregistry oci://ghcr.io/agentregistry-dev/helm/agentregistry
```

The command deploys Agent Registry on the Kubernetes cluster using the default configuration. The [Parameters](#parameters) section lists the values that can be configured during installation.

> **Tip**: List all releases using `helm list`

## Uninstalling the Chart

```console
helm uninstall my-agentregistry
```

> **Note**: If `database.bundled.persistence.keepOnUninstall` is `false` (the default), the PersistentVolumeClaim **will be deleted** and all database data will be lost. Set it to `true` to retain data across `helm uninstall`.

## Architecture

The chart deploys the following Kubernetes resources:

| Resource | Description |
|---|---|
| Deployment | Agent Registry application + bundled PostgreSQL containers |
| Service | Exposes HTTP (`:12121`) and gRPC (`:21212`) ports |
| ConfigMap | Application configuration injected as environment variables |
| Secret | PostgreSQL password and JWT signing key |
| Secret | Kubeconfig for in-cluster agent management |
| ServiceAccount | Dedicated service account for the workload |
| ClusterRole / ClusterRoleBinding | RBAC rules for managing MCP servers, deployments, and services |
| NetworkPolicy | Optional egress/ingress policy (disabled by default) |

## Database

By default the chart deploys a bundled PostgreSQL instance using the `pgvector/pgvector` image (PostgreSQL + pgvector extension). To use an external database instead, disable the bundled instance and provide connection details:

```yaml
database:
  bundled:
    enabled: false
  external:
    host: "my-postgres.example.com"
    database: "agent-registry"
    username: "agentregistry"
    password: "changeme"
```

Or supply a full connection URL:

```yaml
database:
  bundled:
    enabled: false
  external:
    url: "postgresql://agentregistry:changeme@my-postgres.example.com:5432/agent-registry?sslmode=require"
```

## Secrets

By default (`secrets.autoGenerate: true`) the chart generates a random PostgreSQL password and JWT key on first install using Helm's `lookup` function. Alternatively, supply an existing Secret:

```yaml
existingSecret: "my-agentregistry-secret"
```

The Secret must contain the keys `POSTGRES_PASSWORD` and `AGENT_REGISTRY_JWT_PRIVATE_KEY`.

## RBAC

Agent Registry manages MCP servers, agents, deployments, and related resources across namespaces. The chart therefore creates a `ClusterRole`/`ClusterRoleBinding` by default (`rbac.clusterScoped: true`). For single-namespace or multi-tenant deployments, set `rbac.clusterScoped: false` to use a namespace-scoped `Role`/`RoleBinding`.

